	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sat, Apr 20th 7:45 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=61489><span id=Scholar>Kamlatir, Eater of Souls</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>66 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.70]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Wow, I don't even understand this post. I didn't attempt to make a statement about what race is the number one tanking race, sheesh. Let me say this again:<br><br>Large races don't get more hp's per point of sta. (yes, this is very important since I and everyone else with me thought this was the case. I did the experiment mentioned in my first post, it's not some kind of hypothetical quiz)<br><br>Large races start with a higher value of sta.<br><br>The more you advance your character the more the difference between an ogre and a de will lessen.<br><br>Finally, once you reach the point where your sta is at 200 or so you will get shaman buffed to the hard cap when raiding.<br><br>So, to clarify Lunatic, once you reach level 60, get into a guild that kills regularly in ToV (not the common mobs but the named ones), goes to weekend trips to Sleepers, swings by Kael to take out vindi and statue, and so on, once that happens the DE's will approach Ogres in level of hp until the difference is gone.<br><br>Kamlatir<br>60 Grave Lord of Far Seekers<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Sat Apr 20 07:40:33 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
